    dc:description "FIGURES 37–40. 37. Sessiluncus aegypticus Nasr & Affifi, male, modified seta and spur on legs II & III, respectively; 38– 40. Sessiluncus hungaricus, female. 38. Dorsal shield, posterolateral region; 39. Sternal shield, and posterior horse-shoe-like extension of the shield (inset); 40. Peritrematal shield and antrolateral part of ventrianal shield." ;
