    dc:description "FIGURES 3–9. Sessiluncus aegypticus Nasr & Affifi, 3–8. Male; 9. Female. 3. Gnathotectum, followed posteriorly narrow sclerotised band; 4. Chelicera; 5. Tarsus I; 6. Femur II; 7. Genu–tibia II; 8. Femur III; 9. Gnathotectum, followed posteriorly narrow sclerotised band (in specimen from Iran)." ;
